<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.250306>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Celleporaria vermiformis (Waters, 1909), Lebanon, Stn 1 B: A, B, typical aspects of a multilayered colony, with disorderly arranged zooids and raised conical processes; C, primary orifice of non-ovicelled zooid; D, two ovicells and a conical process bearing at its base a minute avicularium facing laterally; E, gigantic adventitious avicularium at the tip of a bulging cystid proximal to the orifice. Scale bars: A, B, 200 µm; C, 50 µm; D, E, 100 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/250306/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

